span.p:
User Input:
M sequences to generate
Energy filter: min/max kcal/mol
(optional)

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p:
Fixed Parameters:
P = 14 bases (stem 5')
Q = 4 bases (loop)
R = 14 bases (stem 3')
S = 21 bases (tail)
Total length = 53 nt

span.p:
1. Generate Random Sequence
P: 14 random bases (A/C/G/T)
Q: 4 random bases
R: reverse complement of P
S: 21 random bases
Computational Energy:
Random number generation

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;
display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
2. RNAfold Prediction
(ViennaRNA 2.7.0)
Temperature: 60C
Input: DNA sequence (53 nt)
Process: Minimum free energy
structure prediction
Algorithm: Dynamic programming
(Zuker algorithm)
Output:
Dot-bracket notation
G (kcal/mol)
Computational Energy:
O(n) time complexity

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p:
3. Parse Structure
Convert dot-bracket to
base pair indices
'(' paired with ')'
'.' unpaired

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p:
4. Structure Validation
Check 1: Designed pairs
P[i] pairs with R[13-i]
(14 Watson-Crick pairs)
Check 2: No extra pairs
Check 3: Loop Q unpaired
(no internal structure)

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;
display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;
display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;
display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;
display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
5. Calculate Fraction Paired
= 1 / (1 + e^(G/RT))
R = 0.001987 kcal/(molK)
T = 333.15 K (60C)
Output: (0-1)
1: fully paired
0.5: equilibrium
0: unpaired

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p:
6. Generate Visualization
RNAplot:
Creates PS/EPS file
2D structure layout
Ghostscript (if available):
Converts PS PNG
Resolution: 300 DPI
Files:
plots/seq_N_ss.ps
plots/seq_N.png

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p:
7. Store Result
Record contains:
ID number
Full sequence (53 nt)
Structure (dot-bracket)
G (kcal/mol)
(fraction paired)
File paths (PS, PNG)

div.style: display: table-cell; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center;

span.p:
8. Save Output Files
resultados.vienna:
Sequence
Structure (G)
resultados_summary.csv:
ID, seq, struct, energy,
theta, ps_path, png_path

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
9. Rank by Stability
(Top 5)
Sort by G (ascending)
Most negative = most stable
Biological significance:
Lower G indicates
thermodynamically
favorable structures

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
10. Rank by Equilibrium
(Top 5)
Sort by | - 0.5|
Closest to 0.5 = equilibrium
Biological significance:
0.5 indicates structures
with balanced folded/unfolded
populations at 60C
